---
import SectionHead from './SectionHead.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import aboutPhoto from '../assets/casey-about.jpg';

const stats = [
  { k: '3+ yrs', v: 'Independent client delivery' },
  { k: '16+',    v: 'Custom Shopify pages' },
  { k: '400+',   v: 'Shopify catalog items' },
  { k: '90+',    v: 'PageSpeed after HubSpot launch' },
];
---

<section class="section" id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <SectionHead
      idx="03"
      kicker="about"
      inlineDescr
      descr="3 years coding"/>

    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about-photo reveal">
        <div class="about-photo-img">
          <Image class="photo" src={aboutPhoto} alt="Casey Hsu portrait" width={1080} height={1620} />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="about-text reveal">
        <h2>Three years building <span class="accent">CMS platforms</span> and <span class="accent">storefronts</span>, from discovery to handoff.</h2>
        <div class="about-para">
          <p>Most of my client work is in <strong>CMS</strong> and e-commerce platforms: Shopify, HubSpot, and WordPress.
            The day-to-day is custom themes, platform migrations, editor-friendly CMS modules, QA, launches, and clean handoff.</p>
          <p>I'm a <strong>Contentful Certified Professional</strong> (with the Personalization Skill Badge) and a <strong>George Brown</strong> Computer Programming and Analysis grad (Dean's List, all terms).
            On the side I build local LLM and automation tooling to speed up my own workflow.</p>
          <p>Before code, I spent ten years as a <strong>sous chef</strong> leading teams of 5-20: hiring, scheduling, budgets, vendors. Calm under deadline comes standard.</p>
          <p class="muted">Currently open to CMS, e-commerce, frontend, and full-stack roles in the Greater Toronto Area or remote within Canada: contract, hybrid, or on-site.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="stats-strip">
          {stats.map((s) => (
            <div class="stat">
              <div class="k">{s.k}</div>
              <div class="v">{s.v}</div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
